      <para id="id18981331">It is important to find out more about conductors and non-conductors before we take a further look at circuits.</para>
      <list id="id17659734" list-type="bulleted">
        <item>CONDUCTORS AND NON-CONDUCTORS</item>
      </list>
      <para id="id17326829">Energy can be transferred by different means. When electricity is “transported” by a particular material, the material is known as a conductor. When a material does not have the capacity to “transport” or conduct electricity, we speak of it as a non-conductor. You can set up testing apparatus to determine whether a material is a conductor or a non-conductor.</para>
      <para id="id19035694">Set up the following incomplete circuit and test the given materials to determine whether they are conductors or non-conductors:</para>
