      <list id="id17363314" list-type="bulleted">
        <item>AN APPARATUS FOR DIMMING A LIGHT BULB</item>
      </list>
      <para id="id19036765">Have you ever wondered how the light in the lounge is dimmed and made brighter? Building some resistance into the circuit does this. Copper is an excellent conductor, because electricity can flow through it with ease. When you use a thinner piece of copper wire as your conductor, there is less space for the electricity to flow. We speak of the resistance in thin copper wire as being higher than the resistance in thicker copper wire. You can create resistance by winding the wire (which has to be a conductor) around a pencil.</para>
